<br>
Get with me in game and I'll make the metal bits for you (it's a very, very low trivial and very inexpensive if you want to just try it yourself) and walk you through the lute body turn in. Forpar has been screwed up on Povar for a while, and I don't know whether they've fixed it, so I can show you where to find him (often not in his usual place) and how to get him to stop long enough for the turn in (he now often walks one of the zone walls, and it's a pain to hand him everything before he walks off on you).<br>
<br>
After you have that lute body, you can do Trak anytime. Just realize that if you do it before you have the other parts done, folks are doing to be disappointed when they kill him for you and find out that you're &quot;final&quot; battle wasn't really. lol. The bright side is that finding the UDB up while there is enough firepower around to help is a hard challenge, so this way you can keep working on that while also working on the other pieces.<br>
<br>
